ar0822-rpi-dkms (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release as a DKMS source package.
  * Driver state at this release:
    - 3840x2160 at up to 40 fps (full resolution), 1920x1080 at up
      to 120 fps (2x2 binning), 10-bit and 12-bit RAW output.
    - 2-lane and 4-lane MIPI CSI-2 at up to 960 Mbps per lane.
    - Experimental eHDR mode (three-exposure on-sensor HDR, companded
      to 12-bit) via the standard V4L2 wide dynamic range control.
    - ar0822 device tree overlay with cam0 and 4lane options.
    - Targeting Linux kernel 6.12 or newer.
    - Validated on Raspberry Pi 4 and 5, Raspberry Pi OS Bookworm
      and Trixie.

 -- Danius Kalvaitis <danius@kurokesu.com>  Thu, 02 Jul 2026 15:02:03 +0300
